  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">There are two letters on this manuscript. The first is a note from Wendell Phillips to Maria Weston Chapman. Phillips gives instructions about an article in the Liberator newspaper on the Episcopal Convention.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In the middle of page one, there is a letter from Maria Weston Chapman presumably to Anne Warren Weston. Chapman asks Anne W. Weston to send in her material for an article. Mrs. Brooks is preparing for an [anti-slavery] fair.</subfield>
